  68,16,"(We shall brand him on the nose) We shall hit him on the nose; and it is said this means: We shall hit him on the face; and it is also said this means: his face will be darkened."
  68,18,"(And made no exception (for the will of Allah)) they forgot to say: Allah willing;"
  68,19,"(Then a visitation) a punishment from your Lord (came upon it) upon the garden (while they slept) and was burned."
  68,20,"(And in the morning it was as if plucked) it was like a dark night."
  68,22,"(Saying: Run unto your field if ye would pluck (the fruit)) before the needy ones come to know about it."
  68,24,"No needy man shall enter it) i.e. the garden (today against you."
  68,28,"(The best among them) in intellect and opinion; and it is also said this means: the older one of them; and it is also said: the most upright among them (said: Said I not unto you: Why glorify ye not (Allah)) why not say: Allah willing? He said this when they made their vow."
  68,29,"(They said: Glorified be our Lord!) We ask forgiveness of our Lord. (Lo! we have been wrong-doers) we harmed ourselves by our transgression and intention to deprive the needy ones and also by failing to say �Allah willing�."
  68,31,"(They said) in unison: (Alas for us! In truth we were outrageous) we were sinful by depriving the needy ones."
  68,32,"(It may be) and �may be� when used in connection with Allah denotes necessity (that our Lord will give us) in the Hereafter in exchange (better than this in place thereof) better than this garden. (Lo! we beseech our Lord) our desire is with Allah."
  68,36,"(What aileth you) O people of Mecca? (How foolishly ye judge!) Evil is what you judge for yourselves!"
  68,37,"(Or have ye a Scripture wherein you learn) wherein you recite"
  68,38,"(That you shall indeed have) in this Scripture (all that ye choose) all you desire in Paradise in the Hereafter?"
  68,40,"(Ask them) O Muhammad (which of them will vouch for that) that they say!"
  68,41,"(Or have they other gods? Then let them bring their other gods if they are truthful) that they will have that which they claim."